This is an early prototype of a massively-parallel implementation of the NEAT
algorithm, written in Taichi. The intention of this library is to provide a
high-performance tool for evolving and activating very large populations of
CPPNs in a way that is project agnostic, customizable, and eaty to use for many
different purposes. It isn't yet fully featured, optimized, or polished for use
by third parties, but perhaps it will get there in time.
